🐙 Kraken Motorsports Website — Purpose and Content Description

The Kraken Motorsports website is a pre‑launch hub for a VR racing‑rig experience that will be installed in a community lounge. The site’s purpose is to introduce the Kraken brand, explain the upcoming racing experience, build hype, gather early supporters, and prepare for Founders Pass sales before the physical rig is built.

The site should feel like a mix of esports team, arcade attraction, and build‑in‑public project, using a dark‑cyan Kraken theme, bold typography, and a slightly chaotic sticker‑bomb aesthetic.

What the website includes
- Hero Landing Section  
  A bold introduction to Kraken Motorsports with the logo, tagline, and “Coming Soon” messaging. Includes links to Discord and social media.

- About the Kraken Rig  
  A clear explanation of what the Kraken Rig will be: a VR racing simulator with a public leaderboard, competitive challenges, and a unique Kraken-themed identity. This section uses mockups and concept art instead of real hardware photos.

- Leaderboard Preview  
  A static, stylized mock leaderboard showing example lap times. This demonstrates the competitive aspect and sets expectations for the future live leaderboard.

- Founders Pass Information  
  A section describing the Founders Pass program, its perks (early access, discounted sessions, name on the rig, VIP queue), and a placeholder button for reserving a pass.

- Branding & Sticker‑Bomb Gallery  
  A visual gallery showing the Kraken logo variations, color palette, tentacle graphics, UI mockups, and sticker‑bomb concepts. This builds the aesthetic identity before the rig exists.

- Countdown Timer  
  A simple countdown to a placeholder launch date, creating anticipation and urgency.

- Social & Contact Section  
  Links to Discord, Instagram, TikTok, and a placeholder email for inquiries or Founders Pass interest.

Purpose of the website
- Build hype for the Kraken Rig before it physically exists.  
- Establish the Kraken Motorsports brand with a strong visual identity.  
- Explain the concept clearly to potential users, supporters, and lounge staff.  
- Collect early interest through Discord and social media.  
- Prepare for Founders Pass sales by showing perks and scarcity.  
- Showcase the vision with mockups, layouts, and UI previews.  
- Serve as a central hub for updates, countdowns, and community engagement.  

The site is intentionally lightweight and future‑proof. All leaderboard data, payment systems, and hardware photos will be added later once the rig is built and launched.

